#ROOM
Vnum     11000
Name     &YThe Gates of Stormwind&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     Towering stone walls rise high into the sky, adorned with the blue and
gold banners of the Alliance. The paved streets of the Trade District lie
just ahead to the north. To the south, the awe-inspiring bridge known as
the Valley of Heroes stretches out toward Elwynn Forest.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11001
Desc      The paved streets of the Trade District await.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11042
Desc      The grand Valley of Heroes bridge spans the water.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11000 2 11000
  Reset E 1 11000 10 16
  Reset E 1 11001 10 12
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11001
Name     &YThe Trade District Square&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You stand in the heart of Stormwind's mercantile center. Cobblestone paths
branch out in several directions, lined with bustling shops, inns, and the
constant chatter of citizens and adventurers alike. To the east stands the
grand Stormwind Bank, and to the west lies the local Auction House. The
air smells of fresh bread from a nearby vendor and the ozone of passing
mages.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11004
Desc      The street continues deeper into the Trade District.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11002
Desc      The grand pillars of the Stormwind Bank invite you in.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11000
Desc      The Gates of Stormwind lead out of the city.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11003
Desc      The sounds of shouting and commerce echo from the Auction House.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11002
Name     &YThe Stormwind Bank&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     Polished marble floors and heavily reinforced teller cages dominate this
imposing structure. Goblins and humans alike operate behind the counters,
managing the wealth of the Alliance. Heavy iron vaults are visible in the
back, guarded heavily by elite footmen.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11001
Desc      You see the bustling Trade District Square.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11000 2 11002
  Reset E 1 11000 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11003
Name     &YThe Stormwind Auction House&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     It is incredibly loud in here. Adventurers from all over Azeroth stand
around shouting prices, inspecting weapons, and trading raw materials.
A raised dais at the back of the room holds several well-dressed
auctioneers who are frantically keeping track of bids and buy-outs.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11001
Desc      You see the bustling Trade District Square.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11001 1 11003
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11004
Name     &YTrade District - North Walk&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The cobblestone street narrows slightly here as it winds toward the darker,
quieter alleyways of the city. A small cheese shop sits to the right, and
a vendor selling brightly colored flowers stands by a small fountain. The
bustle of the main square is slightly muted here.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11013
Desc      A pristine white bridge crosses the canals toward the Cathedral.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11023
Desc      A heavy stone bridge crosses into the smoky Dwarven District.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11001
Desc      The Trade District Square lies to the south.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11005
Desc      A stone bridge crosses the canals toward the Mage Quarter.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11005
Name     &cThe Stormwind Canals&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You stand upon a sturdy stone bridge arching over the clear, flowing
waters of the Stormwind Canals. The rhythmic sound of water lapping
against stone provides a peaceful backdrop. To the east lies the bustling
Trade District, while the scent of ozone and arcane magic drifts from
the Mage Quarter to the west.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11004
Desc      The Trade District awaits.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11006
Desc      The cobblestones turn a deep purple as you enter the Mage Quarter.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    11046
Desc      A heavily guarded stone ramp leads down to the Stockade.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11006
Name     &CMage Quarter - Entrance&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The atmosphere here is markedly different from the rest of the city. The
air hums with a faint, static electricity. Blue and purple banners hang
from the towers, and the citizens walking by wear robes of varying
intricacy. To the south, you hear the lively sounds of a busy tavern.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11005
Desc      The bridge leads back over the canals.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11007
Desc      The sign of the Blue Recluse hangs over a heavy oak door.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11008
Desc      The street opens up into the central square of the Mage Quarter.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11003 2 11006
  Reset E 1 11000 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11007
Name     &YThe Blue Recluse&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This cozy tavern is a favorite haunt for the city's magical practitioners.
Floating candles illuminate the room, casting dancing shadows on the wood
paneled walls. Robed figures sit huddled in booths, whispering in strange
tongues and nursing drinks.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11006
Desc      The street of the Mage Quarter awaits outside.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11002 1 11007
  Reset E 1 11002 10 17
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11008
Name     &CMage Quarter - Central Square&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You stand in the vibrant heart of the Mage Quarter. The cobblestones
form an intricate arcane rune on the ground. To the west, a spiraling
ramp leads up to the majestic Wizard's Sanctum. To the south, a darker,
narrower alley winds toward a less reputable establishment.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11012
Desc      The path winds upward toward the Stormwind Park.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11006
Desc      The street leads back toward the canals.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11010
Desc      An alley leads toward a gloomy looking building.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11009
Desc      The entrance to the Wizard's Sanctum towers before you.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11003 2 11008
  Reset E 1 11000 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11009
Name     &WThe Wizard's Sanctum&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     You stand inside the grand tower of the Wizard's Sanctum. Arcane
runes glow softly on the walls, and the air is thick with the smell of
parchment and ozone. A magical portal shimmers faintly in the center
of the room, connecting Stormwind to distant lands.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11008
Desc      The central square lies outside the tower.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11010
Name     &dThe Slaughtered Lamb&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The atmosphere here is oppressive. The lighting is dim, provided only
by a few sputtering torches. The patrons here speak in hushed, secretive
voices, and they watch you with suspicious eyes. A set of creaky wooden
stairs leads down into the darkness of the crypts.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11008
Desc      The central square provides a welcome escape from the gloom.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    11011
Desc      The stairs descend into the cold crypts.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11011
Name     &dThe Crypts of the Slaughtered Lamb&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    dark indoors~
Desc     The air down here is freezing cold and smells of rotting earth and
brimstone. Skulls line the stone walls. This is the hidden sanctuary of
Stormwind's warlock coven, where dark bargains are struck and forbidden
magic is practiced away from the prying eyes of the guards.
~
#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    11010
Desc      The stairs lead back up to the tavern.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11004 1 11011
  Reset E 1 11004 10 17
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11012
Name     &GPathway to the Park&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The arcane hum of the Mage Quarter begins to fade as the cobblestones
give way to a dirt path lined with vibrant green grass and tall, ancient
trees. A cool breeze blows from the west, carrying the scent of blooming
flowers and the distant sound of the ocean.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11008
Desc      The central square of the Mage Quarter.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11013
Name     &WBridge to the Cathedral Square&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You are walking across a wide, arching bridge made of polished white stone.
Beneath you, the Stormwind Canals flow quietly. Ahead to the north, the
magnificent spires of the Cathedral of Light rise into the sky, a beacon
of hope and faith for the Alliance.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11014
Desc      The entrance to Cathedral Square.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11004
Desc      The Trade District awaits.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11014
Name     &WCathedral Square - Entrance&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The air here feels cleaner, and the general noise of the city is replaced
by hushed, respectful tones and the distant sound of chanting choirs.
The paving stones are pristine white marble. To the north lies the central
fountain of the square.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11015
Desc      A beautiful fountain sits in the center of the square.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11013
Desc      The bridge leads back over the canals.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11008 2 11014
  Reset E 1 11000 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11015
Name     &WCathedral Square - The Light's Fountain&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     A massive, tiered fountain dominates the center of the square. Crystal
clear water cascades down its marble basins, catching the sunlight and
creating faint rainbows. Citizens sit on the edges, praying or enjoying
the peaceful atmosphere.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11019
Desc      The grand steps of the Cathedral of Light.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11017
Desc      The eastern walk of the square.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11014
Desc      The entrance to the square.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11018
Desc      The western walk, leading toward the Orphanage.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11007 3 11015
Reset M 0 11007 3 11015
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11016
Name     &YStormwind City Orphanage&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This large, somewhat cluttered building is a haven for children who lost
their parents during the various wars that have plagued Azeroth. Small
beds are lined up against the walls, and toys are scattered across the
floor. It is loud, chaotic, but filled with love.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11018
Desc      The western walk of Cathedral Square.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset O 0 11007 1 11016
Reset M 0 11007 3 11016
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11017
Name     &WCathedral Square - East Walk&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You walk along the eastern edge of the square. To your right, high stone
walls separate the holy grounds from the rest of the city. A few vendors
here silently peddle candles, holy water, and religious texts.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11015
Desc      The central fountain of the square.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11018
Name     &WCathedral Square - West Walk&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You walk along the western edge of the square. The sounds of children
laughing and shouting can be heard from a building just to the west.
Paladins in training can often be seen jogging through this area.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11015
Desc      The central fountain of the square.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11016
Desc      The doors to the Stormwind Orphanage are wide open.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11019
Name     &WSteps of the Cathedral of Light&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     Wide, sweeping marble stairs lead up to the towering oak doors of the
Cathedral of Light. Flanking the doors are massive statues of heroes who
fell defending humanity. Looking back south, you have a breathtaking
view of the entire square and the fountain below.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11020
Desc      The grand nave of the Cathedral beckons.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11015
Desc      The central fountain of the square.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11008 2 11019
  Reset E 1 11000 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11020
Name     &WThe Cathedral of Light - Nave&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The interior of the Cathedral is awe-inspiring. Massive stained glass
windows cast kaleidoscopic colors across the rows of polished wooden
pews. The ceiling arches impossibly high overhead. The air is thick
with incense, and the echoing chants of priests fill the holy hall.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11021
Desc      The main altar of the Cathedral.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11019
Desc      The steps leading back outside.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    11022
Desc      A dark stairwell leads into the catacombs.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11006 1 11020
  Reset E 1 11005 10 17
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11021
Name     &WThe Cathedral of Light - Altar&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     You stand before the grand altar of the Light. A massive tome rests
upon a golden podium. This is the heart of the Silver Hand in Stormwind,
where the highest ranking Paladins and Priests convene to bless troops,
heal the sick, and plan their crusades against the darkness.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11020
Desc      The grand nave of the Cathedral.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11005 1 11021
  Reset E 1 11006 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11022
Name     &dCathedral Catacombs - Entrance&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    dark indoors~
Desc     The air immediately grows cold and stale as you descend beneath the
Cathedral. Dust coats the stone floor, and the faint light from upstairs
barely penetrates the gloom. These catacombs hold the remains of the
city's most revered archbishops and heroes.
~
#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    11020
Desc      The light of the nave beckons from above.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11023
Name     &cBridge to the Dwarven District&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The air grows tangibly warmer and thicker with soot as you cross this
heavy, reinforced stone bridge. The rhythmic clang of metal striking
metal echoes from the east, drowning out the gentle flow of the canals
below. A paved walkway runs south along the canal toward Old Town.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11024
Desc      The smoggy heart of the Dwarven District.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11029
Desc      The canal walk winds down toward the gritty streets of Old Town.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11004
Desc      The Trade District.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11024
Name     &ODwarven District - Main Avenue&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You are standing in the sweltering, noisy heart of the Dwarven District.
Soot stains the cobblestones, and the air smells strongly of sulfur, hot
iron, and roasted meats. To the north is the open-air forge, to the south
lies the local tavern, and to the east stands a massive, mechanized gate.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11026
Desc      The intense heat of the blacksmith's forge radiates from here.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11027
Desc      A massive gear-shaped doorway leads into the Deeprun Tram.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11025
Desc      The Golden Keg tavern beckons with the smell of ale.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11023
Desc      The bridge leads back to the Trade District.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11010 2 11024
  Reset E 1 11000 10 16
  Reset E 1 11010 10 11
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11025
Name     &OThe Golden Keg&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This tavern is considerably rowdier and louder than the others in the
city. The ceilings are low, the wooden tables are heavily scarred by axes
and spilled ale, and an enormous fire roars in the hearth. Dwarves and
humans alike share tales of battle and boast of their latest kills.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11024
Desc      The smoky avenue of the Dwarven District.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11011 1 11025
  Reset E 1 11009 10 17
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11026
Name     &RThe Open Forge&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The heat in this open-air plaza is almost unbearable. Massive anvils
and roaring furnaces dominate the space, surrounded by racks of glowing
weapons and cooling armor. Sparks fly continuously into the air as the
city's finest smiths ply their trade for the Alliance war machine.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11024
Desc      The main avenue of the district.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11009 1 11026
  Reset E 1 11008 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11027
Name     &WDeeprun Tram - Entrance Hall&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     You stand inside a massive, vaulted chamber filled with whirring gears,
hissing steam pipes, and the smell of grease. This marvel of gnomish
engineering connects Stormwind directly to Ironforge. A wide mechanical
ramp descends deeper underground toward the boarding platforms.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11024
Desc      The main avenue of the Dwarven District.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    11028
Desc      The ramp leads down to the tram platforms.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11028
Name     &WDeeprun Tram - Stormwind Platform&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     You are deep beneath the city. An enormous glass tube stretches out to
the north, disappearing into the dark depths of the ocean. The metal
platform shudders periodically as high-speed trams rocket into the
station, carrying passengers between the two great capitals.
~
#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    11027
Desc      The ramp leads up to the city streets.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11010 2 11028
  Reset E 1 11000 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11029
Name     &cCanals - East Walk&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You are walking along the eastern edge of the Stormwind Canals. To the
north lies the smog and clamor of the Dwarven District, while to the
south, the cobblestones grow uneven and cracked, marking the borders
of Old Town. To the east, a massive, heavily guarded bridge leads to
the awe-inspiring Stormwind Keep.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11023
Desc      The bridge connecting the Trade and Dwarven districts.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11036
Desc      The Great Bridge to Stormwind Keep.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11030
Desc      The unkempt streets of Old Town.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11030
Name     &OOld Town - Main Street&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The pristine, organized feel of the Trade District is entirely absent
here. Old Town is a maze of narrow streets, cramped buildings, and
suspicious characters. Street urchins dart through the alleys, and the
smell of cheap ale drifts from a boisterous tavern to the east.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11029
Desc      The walk along the canals.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11031
Desc      The Pig and Whistle tavern is packed with rowdy patrons.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11032
Desc      A narrow, winding alleyway leads deeper into Old Town.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11031
Name     &OThe Pig and Whistle&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This two-story tavern is infamous throughout Stormwind. It serves as
a gathering place for mercenaries, off-duty guards, and those looking
to buy items that might have recently 'fallen off a wagon'. The floor
is sticky, and the air is thick with smoke and questionable rumors.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11030
Desc      The main street of Old Town.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11014 1 11031
  Reset E 1 11012 10 17
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11032
Name     &dOld Town - Winding Alley&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The street narrows considerably here, choked by tall, overhanging
buildings that block out most of the sunlight. The shadows seem almost
alive. At the end of the alley to the east stands a highly secure,
nondescript stone building guarded by lethal-looking individuals.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11030
Desc      The main street of Old Town.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11033
Desc      The heavily guarded entrance to SI:7.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11013 2 11032
  Reset E 1 11011 10 16
  Reset E 1 11013 10 6
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11033
Name     &dSI:7 Headquarters - Entrance&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     You have stepped into the clandestine headquarters of Stormwind's
intelligence agency, SI:7. The atmosphere is tense and quiet.
Operatives clean weapons, read encoded missives, and train relentlessly.
To the north is a training hall, and a flight of stairs leads up.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11034
Desc      The sounds of blades striking wood come from the training hall.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11032
Desc      The winding alleyway outside.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    11035
Desc      Stairs lead up to the master's office.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11013 2 11033
  Reset E 1 11011 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11034
Name     &dSI:7 Headquarters - Training Hall&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This large, sparsely furnished room is dedicated to the deadly arts.
Racks of throwing knives, poisons, and lockpicks line the walls. In
the center of the room sit heavy wooden target dummies, used by
rogues to practice their ambushes and vital strikes.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11033
Desc      The entrance hall.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11015 1 11034
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11035
Name     &dMaster Mathias Shaw's Office&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This office is surprisingly spartan for the leader of such a powerful
organization. A large desk is covered in maps of Azeroth with various
red markers detailing enemy movements. The windows are shuttered,
plunging the room into perpetual twilight.
~
#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    11033
Desc      The stairs lead back down to the main hall.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11012 1 11035
  Reset E 1 11011 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11036
Name     &WThe Great Bridge to the Keep&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You are crossing a breathtaking stone bridge suspended high above the
water. Blue and gold banners flap violently in the wind. The sheer scale
of Stormwind Keep looms ahead to the east, its high towers touching the
clouds. You can feel the weight of history in the massive stone blocks
beneath your feet.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11037
Desc      The Keep's courtyard awaits.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11029
Desc      The canal walk between the districts.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11018 2 11036
  Reset E 1 11014 10 16
Reset M 0 11018 2 11036
  Reset E 1 11014 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11037
Name     &WStormwind Keep - Courtyard&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You have entered the secure courtyard of Stormwind Keep. The ground is
paved in flawless white marble. Statues of legendary kings and heroes
line the walls, standing as silent sentinels. Directly ahead is the
grand entrance to the Royal Gallery, leading into the heart of the keep.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11038
Desc      The towering doors to the Royal Gallery.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11036
Desc      The Great Bridge leading back to the city proper.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11038
Name     &WStormwind Keep - Royal Gallery&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This vast, echoing hallway is lined with rich crimson carpets and priceless
tapestries depicting the great victories of the Alliance. Polished suits
of armor stand at attention in the alcoves. To the east lies the Throne
Room, to the north is the Royal Library, and to the south is the War Room.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11040
Desc      The quiet calm of the Royal Library.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11039
Desc      The magnificent Throne Room of Stormwind.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11041
Desc      The sounds of tactical planning echo from the War Room.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11037
Desc      The Keep's courtyard.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset O 0 11016 1 11038
Reset M 0 11018 2 11038
  Reset E 1 11014 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11039
Name     &WStormwind Keep - Throne Room&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This chamber commands absolute respect. Sunlight streams through massive
stained-glass windows, illuminating the royal blue carpets that lead up
to an empty, gilded throne. Noblemen, advisors, and elite guards stand
in quiet discussion. The air is heavy with politics and power.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11038
Desc      The Royal Gallery.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11016 1 11039
Reset M 0 11017 1 11039
  Reset E 1 11015 10 3
Reset M 0 11018 2 11039
  Reset E 1 11014 10 16
Reset M 0 11018 2 11039
  Reset E 1 11014 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11040
Name     &WStormwind Keep - Royal Library&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The scent of old parchment and leather binding fills the air. Floor-to-
ceiling bookshelves line the walls, containing the accumulated knowledge
of human history, arcane theory, and theological texts. Scholars speak
in hushed whispers, studying by the light of magical orbs.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11038
Desc      The Royal Gallery.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11041
Name     &WStormwind Keep - War Room&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     A massive wooden table dominates the center of this room, entirely
covered by a highly detailed map of Azeroth. Wooden figurines representing
Horde and Alliance armies are scattered across it. High-ranking officers
shout orders, read scouting reports, and plan the defense of the realm.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11038
Desc      The Royal Gallery.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11019 1 11041
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11042
Name     &YValley of Heroes - North Bridge&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You are walking along the colossal stone bridge that serves as the main
artery into Stormwind. Flanking you are two impossibly massive stone
statues. To the west stands Ranger Captain Alleria Windrunner, and to the
east stands Force Commander Danath Trollbane. The wind howls through
the canyon here.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11000
Desc      The great gates of Stormwind City.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11043
Desc      The center of the grand bridge.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11020 2 11042
  Reset E 1 11000 10 16
Reset M 0 11021 1 11042
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11043
Name     &YValley of Heroes - Center&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The center of the grand bridge is dominated by the most prominent statue
of them all: General Turalyon, his stone sword raised high in eternal
defiance. The roaring waterfalls on either side of the bridge create a
constant, thunderous roar that fills the valley.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11042
Desc      The northern span of the bridge.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11044
Desc      The southern span of the bridge.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset O 0 11017 1 11043
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11044
Name     &YValley of Heroes - South Bridge&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The southern end of the bridge marks the transition from the wild forests
of Elwynn to the civilized heart of humanity. Two more colossal statues
stand guard here: Archmage Khadgar to the west, and Kurdran Wildhammer
atop his gryphon to the east.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11043
Desc      The center of the grand bridge.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11045
Desc      The dirt path leading into Elwynn Forest.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset M 0 11020 2 11044
  Reset E 1 11000 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11045
Name     &GElwynn Forest - City Outskirts&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The grand cobblestones of Stormwind give way to the worn dirt paths of
Elwynn Forest. Towering pines and oaks surround the valley entrance.
Looking north, the sheer scale of the Valley of Heroes and the white
walls of Stormwind is enough to take a traveler's breath away.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11044
Desc      The Valley of Heroes bridge begins here.
~
#ENDEXIT

#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    12020
Desc      The road continues into Elwynn Forest.
~
#ENDEXIT

#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11046
Name     &WOutside the Stormwind Stockade&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     A heavy iron portcullis blocks the way into the high-security prison
known as the Stockade. The guards here look tense, as if a riot could
break out at any moment. Through the bars, a glowing portal stone
swirls with instance energy.
~
#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    11005
Desc      The stone ramp leads back up to the canals.
~
#ENDEXIT

Reset O 0 11018 1 11046
